Class CodeGenerator

  • java.lang.Object
    • CodeGenerator

  • public class CodeGenerator
extends java.lang.Object
    Effectively compile the miniRust code to assembly Use of registry : - R0 : Use for calculations, print and all sort of things - R1 : Use for binary operations (along with stack) - R2 : None - R3 : None - R4 : Use for saving sign of int to print - R5 : Mode for printing (0 : int, 1 : boolean, 2 : String, 3 : CRLF) - R6 : Use as temporary registry for printing - R7 : Contains a copy of current value while printing
    Author:
    frosqh
